name: Vrundavan Pure veg. Restaurant

reviews.review_text: I like to visit this pure vegetarian restaurant for breakfast local Goan + South Indian +++ & their simple yet tasty lunch preparations & options, complete meals at a full value for money price, they also have a great snack counter at the cashier desk

Walking distance from Mapusa bus stand
2 to 3 minute walking distance near Petrol / Fuel station.

In morning All South Indian breakfast served and price is affordable.
Idli 50 rupees
Butter Paper masala dhosa 100

Nice quality and quantity pure veg.

For lunch also nice quantity and nice quality.

Highly recommend
10/10

Service is so good. Well neat and clean. Pure vegetarian food and other beverage. Everything from breakfast to dinner you will get here.
I must say this is best vegetarian restaurant in mapusa infront of municipal garden, Mapusa.

It's close on Tuesday.
Open Time...
Wednesday to Monday
From 7 am to 10:30 pm.

description:
### Discovering Vrundavan Pure Veg Restaurant: A Vegetarian Haven in Goa

Nestled in the tranquil vicinity of Assonora, Goa, **Vrundavan Pure Veg Restaurant** has made a name for itself among the locals and visitors alike, achieving a respectable rating of **3.9** from **1,253 reviews**. Renowned for its **affordable prices**, delectable **breakfast options**, and famous **pav bhaji**, this pure vegetarian sanctuary beckons foodies seeking wholesome and flavorsome meals in an inviting setting.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering Vrundavan, patrons are greeted by a clean and well-maintained establishment. The décor, highlighting simple yet aesthetic design elements, creates a cozy atmosphere perfect for casual dining. The lighting strikes a balance, providing warmth without being overwhelming, and the restaurant's layout encourages a communal feel, reminiscent of a familial dining experience typical in Indian culture. Reviews hint at a pleasant atmosphere enhanced by light-hearted music, which, combined with the subtly fragrant aroma of food, sets a delightful background for diners.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Vrundavan boasts a diverse menu, featuring an array of **South Indian** and **local Goan breakfast** options, making it a favorite spot for early risers. Signature dishes such as **idli** (₹50) and **butter paper masala dosa** (₹100) are consistently praised for their quality and portion size—testaments to the restaurant's commitment to offering **value for money**. Their lunch offerings maintain the same standard, serving hearty **pure vegetarian meals** that continuously receive high marks for both quality and quantity. The freshly prepared snacks at the storefront counter also delight customers, allowing for a quick bite as one waits to be seated.

### Customer Experience & Service

The service at Vrundavan is another reason patrons return, with numerous reviews applauding the staff's friendliness and efficiency. Customers appreciate the meticulous attention to cleanliness, making it a comfortable dining venue. The establishment operates from Wednesday to Monday, providing ample opportunity for guests to enjoy meals from **7 AM to 10:30 PM**, with the only closure occurring on Tuesdays. 

### Popularity & Reviews

The buzz surrounding Vrundavan is palpable—frequent mentions of its cleanliness and flavor have cemented its reputation as one of the best vegetarian restaurants in Mapusa. Guests rave about their experiences on social media, showcasing their delightful meals and the restaurant's inviting atmosphere. Notably, the recognition it receives from both locals and visitors stands as a testament to its consistent culinary excellence.

### Utilizing Visual Content

Images accompanying customer reviews vividly capture the essence of Vrundavan. The vibrant presentation of dishes invites diners into a world of taste, where every plate becomes a feast for the eyes. One can discern from the photographs how the idlis are served with a generous side of chutneys and sambar, while the dosas are artfully arranged, emphasizing both care and creativity in dishing them out. Reviews also highlight the neat presentation of the dining area, projecting an image of hospitality and attention to detail.

In conclusion, **Vrundavan Pure Veg Restaurant** is not just a place to eat; it's an experience rich with flavors, community, and cultural essence. Its combination of quality vegetarian cuisine, commendable service, and inviting ambiance make it a worthwhile stop for anyone in the area, living up to the mantra of being a **value-for-money dining** destination. Whether it’s for breakfast, lunch, or a casual snack, Vrundavan promises a satisfying vegetarian experience that's sure to leave a lasting impression.
